      "span_text": "However, the typing morphism is more flexible than the traditional one  : a C-typed graph edge e can be incident to any C-typed graph node v as long as its typing edge t E (e) (in C) is incident to a node type v (also in C), such that t V (v) and v are connected under the inheritance order relation (i.e., t V (v) * V C v )."
